(19, 1, '2013-11-13 21:22:12', '2013-11-13 21:22:12', '<!--:en-->What is Spirulina?\r\n\r\nSpirulina is a spiral coil shaped, blue-green, micro algae (0.2 - 0.3mm in size), which grows naturally in some alkaline lakes, in both tropical and subtropical climates around the world.\r\n\r\nSpirulina has evolved over the past 3.6 billion years on Earth.\r\nScientists say that microorganisms like Spirulina generated our oxygen.\r\nSpirulina has been harvested and consumed for centuries by local populations.\r\nSpirulina was a food source for the Aztecs as late as the 16th century.\r\nSpirulina may have an even longer history in Chad (Africa), dating back to the 9th century.<!--:-->', 'Shop', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '4-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-13 21:22:12', '2013-11-13 21:22:12', '', 4, 'http://localhost/spiralps.ch/uncategorized/4-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(21, 1, '2013-11-13 21:24:40', '2013-11-13 21:24:40', '<!--:en--><strong>Spirulina</strong> is a spiral coil shaped, blue-green, micro algae (0.2 - 0.3mm in size), which grows naturally in some alkaline lakes, in both tropical and subtropical climates around the world.\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Spirulina has evolved over the past 3.6 billion years on Earth. </strong></li>\r\n	<li>Scientists say that microorganisms like Spirulina generated our oxygen.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Spirulina has been harvested and consumed for centuries by local populations.</strong></li>\r\n	<li>Spirulina was a food source for the Aztecs as late as the 16th century.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Spirulina may have an even longer history in Chad (Africa), dating back to the 9th century.\r\n</strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\nSpirulina is currently in daily use regionally and used to make broths for meals. It is harvested from small lakes and ponds around Lake Chad and then dried into cakes called dihé, which are sold in local markets.\r\n\r\nAlthough Spirulina has always been consumed regionally, it has only gained a wider, more popular worldwide appeal, recently. In 1974, Spirulina was declared by the United Nations World Food Conference as the "best food for the future", and is now consumed by health conscious people all over the world.<!--:-->', '<!--:en-->10 bottles<!--:-->', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '10-bottles', '', '', '2013-11-14 16:23:27', '2013-11-14 16:23:27', '', 0, 'http://localhost/spiralps.ch/?post_type=product&#038;p=21', 0, 'product', '', 0),
(22, 1, '2013-11-13 21:25:04', '2013-11-13 21:25:04', '<!--:en--><strong>Spiralps® is a new type of natural drink, the first of its kind containing fresh microalgae Spirulina. </strong>\r\n\r\nThe fresh Spirulina in Spiralps® not only tastes great, (far better than any dried form) it is nutritionally superior, too!\r\n\r\nOur Spirulina is <strong> not cultivated out in an open pond, but in a controlled environment, to guarantee the highest quality.</strong> Furthermore, our Spirulina has <strong>never been heated</strong>, thanks to an advanced high-pressure pasteurization system that preserves nutritional values.\r\n\r\nSpiralps® is produced in <strong>Switzerland</strong> and contains herb-extracts from the pristine Alps and organic-fruits, combining the benefits of all these raw ingredients, to deliver more, natural vitamins, carotenoids, antioxidants, and fibers.\r\n\r\n<strong>Spiralps® is THE solution for consumers that are looking for a "wellness" drink that helps them boost their vital-energy level, fight fatigue, combat stress, and live healthy.</strong><!--:-->', '<!--:en-->20 bottles<!--:-->', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', '20-bottles', '', '', '2013-11-14 16:29:23', '2013-11-14 16:29:23', '', 0, 'http://localhost/spiralps.ch/?post_type=product&#038;p=22', 0, 'product', '', 0),
