Highest concentration of protein by weight of any food thus far studied.</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Vitamins</h2>\r\nVitamin A,\r\nB1 (thiamine),\r\nB2 (riboflavin),\r\nB3 (niacin),\r\nB6 (pyridoxine),\r\nB12 (Cyanocobalamin),\r\nD, E, K,\r\nFolate, Biotin,\r\nPantothenic Acid, Beta Carotene (source of vitamin A), Inositol</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Minerals</h2>\r\nContains a full spectrum of minerals like:\r\nMagnesium,\r\nZinc,\r\nSelenium,\r\nChromium,\r\nManganese,\r\nGermanium,\r\nand it is rich in Iron.</td>\r\n<td>\r\n<h2>Others</h2>\r\nPhytopigments and Antioxidants:\r\n-Carotenoids\r\n-Phycocyanin, Chlorophyl\r\n-Xanthophylls, Zeaxanthin\r\n\r\nFatty acids &amp; Enzymes:\r\n-Gamma Linolenic (GLA)\r\n-Omega 3 &amp; 6\r\n-Essential Linoleic\r\n-SOD Superoxide Dismutase</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table><!--:-->', '<!--:en-->What is Spirulina?<!--:--><!--:de-->What is Spirulina?<!--:--><!--:fr-->What is Spirulina?<!--:-->', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'open', '', '24-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-21 20:41:00', '2013-11-21 20:41:00', '', 24, 'http://localhost/spiralps.ch/uncategorized/24-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
